Afrihost has announced that the pricing of its monthly broadband packages – excluding Rain products – will increase on 1 April. The company said the continued upward pressure of inflation on its costs over the years has forced it to increase prices. The price changes are as follows: “It’s our goal to provide the best products and service in South Africa, and this price adjustment will enable us to continue to strive to bring you the best Internet experience possible,” said Afrihost CEO Gian Visser.